  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by partially restoring the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the sentencing guidelines for this amount suggest a term of confinement balanced with rehabilitation. The outburst from the spectator is disregarded as it is legally irrelevant to the determination of an appropriate sentence. Taking into account the defendant's clean record and partial restitution, a period of 6 months is sufficient to serve as a deterrent and punishment without being overly punitive.",
